Title: Netter's Atlas of Human Embryology
Author: ফ্রাঙ্ক এইচ. নিটার
Summary:
Netter's Atlas of Human Embryology
With more than 300 medical illustrations and schematics, tables, and text, this atlas includes coverage of the major processes, events, and concepts related to normal and abnormal embryonic development. It emphasizes the morphological patterns in the embryo and fetus.
